B6</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Visa fees are not included.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p>From sun-soaked beaches to vibrant nightlife, Cyprus is perfect for those craving a blend of relaxation and excitement.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Aqaba, Jordan Travel Package &ndash; Starting $880</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Dive into history, adventure, and breathtaking landscapes with our <strong>Aqaba tour</strong>. This 5-day/6-night package showcases the best of Jordan.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>🛫 Flight:</strong> Royal Jordanian</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>🏨 Stay:</strong> Handpicked hotel accommodation</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Inclusions:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Meet and assist at Aqaba Airport</li>\r\n	<li>Private airport-hotel-airport transfers</li>\r\n	<li>Travel insurance</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>📅 Itinerary Highlights:</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 1:</strong> Arrival in Aqaba</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 2:</strong> Aqaba city tour (8&ndash;10 hours, car + driver)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 3:</strong> Full-day Petra tour</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 4:</strong> Wadi Rum desert adventure</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 5:</strong> Free leisure day</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Day 6:</strong> Departure</p>\r\n\r\n<p><em>Entry fees and meals not included.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>🚤 Optional Activities:</h3>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Yacht Tour with Lunch: $100/person</li>\r\n	<li>Glass Boat Snorkeling Tour: $170/person</li>\r\n	<li>Diving (25&ndash;40 min): $170/person</li>\r\n	<li>Parasailing: $70/person</li>\r\n	<li>Jet Ski: $50/person</li>\r\n	<li>Banana Boat: $15/person</li>\r\n	<li>Snorkeling Trip: $35/person</li>\r\n	<li>Water Ski: $35/person</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>This adventure-packed trip is perfect for travelers looking to combine nature, history, and leisure in one unforgettable journey.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Why Book with World Wide Travel?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>As a leading <strong>travel agency in Lebanon</strong>, World Wide Travel is committed to delivering high-quality, affordable, and reliable <strong>travel packages from Lebanon</strong>. Our strong relationships with hotels, airlines, and activity providers allow us to bring you the best value every season.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>✔ Trusted local and international partners</p>\r\n\r\n<p>✔ Tailored packages for every budget</p>\r\n\r\n<p>✔ Customer-first travel planning</p>\r\n\r\n<p>✔ 24/7 support before and during your trip</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Book Your Summer Getaway Now!</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Whether you&#39;re interested in lounging on Cyprus beaches or exploring the wonders of Jordan, our <strong>affordable travel packages</strong> are the perfect solution. With <strong>travel packages from Lebanon</strong> starting from just $700, now is the time to secure your summer holiday.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>🔗 Contact World Wide Travel to book your <a href=\"https://worldwidetravel-lb.com/packages/2/where-to-travel\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>summer travel package</strong> today!</a></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Frequently Asked Questions</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Q: Are these packages customizable?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Yes, we can tailor any package based on your preferences, including additional days, activities, or destinations.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Q: Do I need a visa for Cyprus or Jordan?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Visa requirements vary by nationality. We can guide you through the process and assist with documentation.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Q: Are meals included?</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>Hotel stays are on a BB (Bed &amp; Breakfast) basis. Optional excursions include meals where noted.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',1,'2025-05-26 10:42:41','2025-05-26 10:42:41'),
(52,'How Dubai\'s New Visa Centre Sets a Global Standard for Travel & Immigration Services in the Middle East','Visa & Immigration',NULL,'2025-05-26',0,NULL,'<p>Dubai has once again positioned itself at the forefront of global travel innovation with the launch of the world&rsquo;s largest visa application centre, located in the vibrant Wafi City district. This state-of-the-art facility, operated by VFS Global, isn&rsquo;t just about scale&mdash;it represents a revolution in how visa services are delivered to millions of travelers worldwide. By integrating advanced technology with exceptional customer experience, Dubai is setting new standards for global mobility that promise to transform the travel industry.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Spanning nearly 150,000 square feet, the centre can process up to 10,000 visa applications daily, making it the highest-capacity visa facility anywhere on the planet. With more than 200 submission counters and a diverse team of over 400 professionals from 25+ nationalities, the centre serves 37 client governments, consolidating what used to be a fragmented process into a seamless, one-stop destination for travelers and governments&nbsp;alike</p>',1,'2025-05-26 11:06:52','2025-05-27 09:38:10'),
(53,'Asia, Europe, Middle East, And North America Face Growing New Threat From Travel Payment Fraud And Fake Hotel Offers Targeting Vacationers','International Travel Risk',NULL,'2025-05-26',0,NULL,'<p>Fraud Risk Peaks During Holiday Seasons</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The report also reveals that fraud tends to spike during peak travel periods. Holidays and busy vacation seasons make travelers more likely to search for special deals, putting them at greater risk of falling prey to fraud.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Mastercard&rsquo;s internal data shows that fraud rates increase by more than eighteen percent during the summer months, a time when many people flock to popular vacation spots. Likewise, fraud incidents rise by over twenty-eight percent in winter destinations during colder months.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>These seasonal patterns highlight the importance of exercising extra caution when booking travel during high-demand periods and the need for the travel industry to strengthen fraud prevention efforts at these times.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>How Travelers Can Protect Themselves</p>\r\n\r\n<p>As travel fraud continues to rise, it is crucial for travelers to take proactive steps to safeguard themselves. Booking through reputable platforms, verifying the authenticity of offers, and using secure payment methods can help minimize the risk of being scammed.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>The travel industry also has a responsibility to help protect customers. Investing in advanced technologies, such as AI-powered fraud detection systems, and ensuring greater transparency in listings can help reduce fraudulent activity.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Travelers across Asia, Europe, the Middle East, and North America are facing a growing threat from fraud, with scammers targeting payment transactions and fake hotel offers. This rising trend puts vacationers at risk long before they embark on their journeys.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>While the allure of travel remains strong, there is a growing need for heightened awareness and robust security measures to ensure that travelers&rsquo; dreams are not derailed by fraud.<br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>',1,'2025-05-26 11:09:36','2025-05-26 11:09:36'),
(60,'EU Entry/Exit System (EES): Passport Stamps Are Ending – What Lebanon Travelers Need to Know',NULL,NULL,'2025-08-22',0,NULL,'<h1>EU Entry/Exit System (EES): Passport Stamps Are Ending — What Lebanon Travelers Need to Know</h1>\r\n<p>Starting <strong>October 12, 2025</strong>, Europe begins rolling out the <strong>Entry/Exit System (EES)</strong> and will gradually phase out passport stamps across <strong>29 countries</strong>. For travelers from Lebanon, EES means faster, biometric border checks and new data capture (facial image, fingerprints, entry/exit records) when crossing external Schengen borders. Full implementation is expected by <strong>April 10, 2026</strong>. <em>(Source: Travel + Leisure, Aug 6, 2025)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<h2>What is the EES and who does it affect?</h2>\r\n<p>EES is a digital border system for <strong>non-EU nationals</strong> traveling short-stay to the Schengen area. It replaces physical stamps with electronic records, improving security and reducing queues. Countries adopting EES include Austria, Belgium, Bulgaria, Croatia, Czechia, Denmark, Estonia, Finland, France, Germany, Greece, Hungary, Iceland, Italy, Latvia, Liechtenstein, Lithuania, Luxembourg, Malta, Netherlands, Norway, Poland, Portugal, Romania, Slovakia, Slovenia, Spain, Sweden and Switzerland.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>How it changes your trip from Lebanon</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li><strong>No more ink stamps:</strong> expect biometric capture on first entry post-launch, plus automated entry/exit logs.</li>\r\n  <li><strong>Border timing:</strong> first-time EES enrollment may add a few minutes; later crossings should be quicker.</li>\r\n  <li><strong>Documents:</strong> valid passport, visas if applicable; ensure <em>passport validity</em> and <em>biometrics readiness</em>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Other countries moving to digital borders</h2>\r\n<p>The UK has launched its <strong>Electronic Travel Authorization (ETA)</strong>; the US is expanding <strong>TSA facial recognition</strong>; and <strong>Australia, Singapore, Hong Kong, Argentina</strong> already operate without routine passport stamps. <em>(Source: T+L)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Practical tips & how we can help</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li>Check airline and airport guidance before you fly.</li>\r\n  <li>Allow extra time on your first EES visit.</li>\r\n  <li>Keep confirmations (hotels/insurance/itineraries) handy in case of questions.</li>\r\n  <li>We can plan your trip and advise requirements — <a href=\"{{ url(\'/contact\') }}\">contact our Beirut team</a>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Related trips from Lebanon</h2>\r\n<p>Explore our European packages: \r\n  <a href=\"{{ url(\'/package/prague\') }}\">Prague City Break</a>, \r\n  <a href=\"{{ url(\'/package/vienna\') }}\">Vienna Christmas Markets</a>, \r\n  <a href=\"{{ url(\'/package/istanbul\') }}\">Istanbul</a>, \r\n  <a href=\"{{ url(\'/package/ayia-napa-or-limassol\') }}\">Cyprus (Ayia Napa/Limassol)</a>.\r\n</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>FAQs</h2>\r\n<h3>Do I still get my passport stamped?</h3>\r\n<p>No. With EES, most non-EU travelers will not receive manual stamps; the system logs entries/exits electronically.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>When does EES start and finish rolling out?</h3>\r\n<p>Rollout starts <strong>Oct 12, 2025</strong> and is expected to be fully live by <strong>Apr 10, 2026</strong>. <em>(T+L)</em></p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Is ETIAS also required?</h3>\r\n<p>ETIAS (a separate pre-travel authorisation) is expected in a later phase; timelines are managed by the EU and may change. Check before booking.</p>\r\n“Published Aug 6, 2025,  <a hef=\"https://www.travelandleisure.com/passport-stamps-are-disappearing-across-29-countries-this-fall-11785316\"Travel + Leisure” </a>',1,'2025-08-22 17:09:01','2025-08-22 17:09:01'),
(62,'spain Leads Europe in AI‑Powered Travel Planning – What It Means for Lebanon',NULL,NULL,'2025-09-04',0,NULL,'<h1>Spain Leads Europe in AI‑Powered Travel Planning &ndash; What It Means for Lebanese Travelers</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>According to a recent barometer report by Europ Assistance and Ipsos, Spain is at the forefront of <strong>AI travel planning</strong> in Europe. About <strong>20% of Spanish travellers</strong> have used AI tools to book or plan a holiday &ndash; higher than the European average of 16%. This study suggests that AI could help Lebanese tourists optimise their trips to Spain with personalised itineraries, accommodation suggestions and activity recommendations.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>How Spanish Travelers Are Using AI</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>48% use AI</strong> for accommodation suggestions</li>\r\n	<li><strong>47%</strong> for destination information</li>\r\n	<li><strong>37%</strong> to create itineraries</li>\r\n	<li><strong>33%</strong> for activity ideas</li>\r\n	<li><strong>26%</strong> for booking recommendations</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Why Spain&rsquo;s Tech‑Forward Approach Matters</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Spain&rsquo;s robust tourism infrastructure and openness to innovation have enabled quicker adoption of AI tools. These tools analyse user data to deliver unique travel experiences, something traditional agencies or guidebooks can&rsquo;t always match. For Lebanese travellers planning a European getaway, AI can streamline decisions on where to stay, what to see, and how to optimise time and budget.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Adoption Across Europe &amp; Privacy Concerns</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Although Spanish adoption of AI travel planners is higher, the European average sits at 16%. Roughly 26% of Spanish respondents say they&rsquo;ll likely use AI in the future, compared with a 21% European average. However, <strong>39% of Spaniards</strong> remain cautious about privacy and trust issues, mirroring concerns across Europe.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Plan Your Tech‑Enhanced Trip</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Ready to explore Spain with AI assistance? Check out our packages: <a href=\"{{ url(\'/package/andalusia\') }}\">Andalusia &amp; Southern Spain</a>, <a href=\"{{ url(\'/package/prague\') }}\">Prague</a>, and <a href=\"{{ url(\'/package/vienna\') }}\">Vienna</a>. These links help search engines understand your site structure and give readers a clear next step.</p>',0,'2025-09-03 21:02:02','2025-11-04 08:33:19'),
(63,'India & China to Restart Direct Flights and Boost Trade – Impacts on Lebanon',NULL,NULL,'2025-09-04',0,NULL,'<h1>India & China to Restart Direct Flights and Boost Trade – What It Means for Lebanon</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>India and China have agreed to resume direct flights and strengthen trade and investment ties after years of disruption. The announcement followed meetings between Chinese Foreign Minister Wang Yi and India’s National Security Advisor Ajit Doval in New Delhi. For travellers and businesses in Lebanon, this development could mean better flight connections and expanded economic opportunities in Asia.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Key Outcomes of the Talks</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n  <li><strong>Direct flights</strong> will restart after being halted since the COVID‑19 outbreak.</li>\r\n  <li><strong>Border trade reopening:</strong> three border points will re‑open for commerce and improved visa processing is planned.</li>\r\n  <li><strong>Border negotiations:</strong> both sides will form a working group to address troop deployments along the Himalayan border and to discuss demarcation issues.</li>\r\n  <li><strong>Upcoming events:</strong> Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi will visit China for the Shanghai Cooperation Organisation summit later this month.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Impacts on Travel & Business</h2>\r\n<p>The return of direct flights between India and China will reduce layover times and may introduce new routes attractive to Lebanese business travellers. Reopened trade could also expand supply chains for Lebanese companies seeking goods like fertilizers, rare earth elements and tunnelling equipment.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Water & Environmental Issues</h2>\r\n<p>India raised concerns over China’s construction of a dam on the Yarlung Zangbo (Brahmaputra) River in Tibet, which could impact downstream countries. China agreed to share emergency river data and continue technical discussions on water issues.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Stay Informed & Travel Smart</h2>\r\n<p>To make the most of improved Asia connections, explore our Asia packages: <a href=\"{{ url(\'/package/aqaba-jordan\') }}\">Jordan: Aqaba & Petra</a>, <a href=\"{{ url(\'/package/honeymoon-sri-lanka\') }}\">Sri Lanka Honeymoon</a> and <a href=\"{{ url(\'/package/maldives\') }}\">Maldives</a>. We’ll update you on flight options when the India–China route reopens.</p>',1,'2025-09-03 21:06:07','2025-09-03 21:06:07'),
(65,'Ryanair Goes Digital-Only on Nov 12, 2025',NULL,NULL,'2025-10-04',0,NULL,'<h1> Ryanair ends paper boarding passes on Nov 12, 2025: A guide for Lebanese travelers</h1> \r\n<p>Starting 12 November 2025, Ryanair will stop accepting printed boarding passes and move fully to digital passes via the myRyanair app. Airport check-in will cost extra, so travelers should check in online and save their mobile pass before heading to the airport.</p>\r\n<p>Starting 12 November 2025, Ryanair will stop accepting printed boarding passes and move fully to digital passes via the myRyanair app. Airport check-in will cost extra, so travelers should check in online and save their mobile pass before heading to the airport.</p>\r\n<h2>What exactly is changing?</h2>\r\n<p>Only digital passes: You must check in online and present the boarding pass in the myRyanair app. Screenshots/Wallet may help at gates, but the app is the primary method. \r\neuronews\r\n\r\nAirport check-in fee applies if you arrive without a digital pass.</p>\r\n<h2> Timeline</h2>\r\n<p>Policy date: 12 Nov 2025 (postponed from early November to ease the transition during mid-term traffic). </p>\r\n<h2>Tips for passengers from Lebanon (BEY and beyond)</h2>\r\n<p>Install & log in to the myRyanair app at home; complete online check-in and download the pass to your phone. </p>\r\n<p>Carry a power bank; keep your phone 50%+ before boarding.</p>\r\n<p>Enable data/roaming or Wi-Fi access at the airport to refresh passes if needed.</p>\r\n<p>Travelling with family members who aren’t tech-savvy? Add their bookings to your app so you can present all passes on one device.</p>\r\n<p>If digital-only feels inconvenient, consider alternative airlines that still allow printed passes on the same route. </p>\r\n<h2>FAQs</h2>\r\n<p>Do I need a smartphone to fly Ryanair now?</p>\r\n<p>Yes—Ryanair is moving to app-based boarding passes only.</p>\r\n<p>What if my phone battery dies?</p>\r\n<p>Airport teams may help if you completed online check-in, but you could face delays/fees. Bring a power bank.</p>\r\n<p>Can I still check in at the airport?</p>\r\n<p>Yes, but it’s charged. Online check-in + app pass is recommended.</p>',1,'2025-10-04 13:08:09','2025-10-04 13:08:09'),
(66,'Lebanon to Integrate AI Into Tourism (MoU Signed)',NULL,NULL,'2025-10-04',0,NULL,'<h1>Lebanon&rsquo;s Tourism &amp; AI Ministries sign MoU to deploy AI solutions</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>On June 4, 2025, Lebanon&rsquo;s Ministry of Technology &amp; AI and Ministry of Tourism signed a memorandum of understanding to introduce AI-powered services and digitize key processes in the tourism sector. The move supports the national digital transition agenda and follows broader calls for &ldquo;smart government.&rdquo;</p>\r\n\r\n<h1>What the agreement aims to deliver</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>Modernize visitor services with new apps and digital tools for tourists and locals.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Digitize ministry workflows for greater efficiency and transparency.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Align with national initiatives promoting smart governance and administrative digitization.</p>\r\n\r\n<h1>Why it matters for travelers &amp; operators</h1>\r\n\r\n<h1>&nbsp;</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>Faster permits &amp; services (e-services for guides, events, and attractions).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Richer trip planning (smart itineraries, digital passes, live updates).</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Better data for destinations, helping spread demand beyond peak hotspots.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Context</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The announcement aligns with Lebanon&rsquo;s recent digital-transformation push and high-level remarks urging an accelerated shift to smart government.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>FAQs</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>When will travelers feel the change?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Rollouts typically happen in phases; expect pilots and apps before wide adoption.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Will services be multilingual?</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Government travel apps in Lebanon commonly support Arabic, English, and French; AI projects are expected to follow suit. (Inference based on policy direction; confirm at launch.)</p>',0,'2025-10-04 13:15:42','2025-12-01 09:40:18'),
(67,'MEA Celebrates 80 Years – New Aircraft, Modern Beirut Airport Upgrades & Launch of Fly Beirut','Travel News',NULL,'2025-11-15',0,NULL,'<p><strong>Middle East Airlines (MEA Lebanon)</strong> has officially celebrated its <strong>80th anniversary</strong>, marking a major milestone for Lebanon&rsquo;s national carrier. During a special ceremony at <strong>Rafik Hariri International Airport &ndash; Beirut (BEY)</strong>, MEA Chairman <strong>Mohammad El-Hout</strong> announced several strategic upgrades aimed at strengthening <strong>Beirut&rsquo;s role as a regional aviation hub</strong> and improving the overall travel experience for Lebanese passengers and visitors.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>✈️ Six New Aircraft Joining MEA&rsquo;s Fleet in 2026</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>MEA confirmed that <strong>six brand-new aircraft</strong> will be added next year, enhancing flight capacity, fuel efficiency, and long-haul performance. This fleet renewal supports MEA&rsquo;s long-term vision of modernizing its operations and improving reliability on popular routes such as:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Beirut &rarr; Dubai</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Beirut &rarr; Istanbul</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Beirut &rarr; Paris</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Beirut &rarr; Doha</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Beirut &rarr; Cairo</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>These aircraft upgrades help MEA compete more effectively with major regional carriers.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>✈️ &ldquo;Fly Beirut&rdquo; &ndash; Lebanon&rsquo;s New Low-Cost Airline</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>One of the biggest announcements was the launch of <strong>Fly Beirut</strong>, a <strong>new low-cost airline in Lebanon</strong> operating under the MEA umbrella.<br />\r\nFly Beirut will:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Offer <strong>budget-friendly fares</strong></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Maintain MEA&rsquo;s <strong>high safety standards</strong></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Target travelers flying to and from <strong>Lebanon, the Gulf, Turkey, and Europe</strong></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>This move positions Beirut as a more competitive travel hub, especially against low-cost carriers in the region.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>🏫 MEA Donates $800,000 to Public Schools in Lebanon</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>As part of its community program, MEA will support <strong>80 Lebanese public schools</strong>, each receiving <strong>$10,000</strong>. This initiative reinforces the company&rsquo;s long-standing commitment to education and social development.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>🌐 Beirut Airport Modernization: Smart Gates, New Lounges &amp; Infrastructure Upgrades</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Lebanon&rsquo;s Minister of Public Works and Transport, <strong>Fayez Rassamni</strong>, highlighted several ongoing projects at <strong>Beirut Airport</strong> aimed at improving efficiency and enhancing passenger comfort:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>New <strong>smart technologies</strong> for faster immigration</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Upgraded <strong>departure halls</strong></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Modernized <strong>VIP lounges</strong></p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>New cultural and artistic installations</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Improved airport access roads</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Reactivation of the <strong>Aviation Safety Center</strong> with ICAO support</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>These upgrades will help Beirut Airport meet rising travel demand while strengthening safety and operational standards.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>🇱🇧 MEA&rsquo;s Role in Lebanon&rsquo;s Future</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Prime Minister <strong>Nawaf Salam</strong> praised MEA as &ldquo;a symbol of Lebanese resilience,&rdquo; stressing its importance in connecting Lebanon to the world. He confirmed the government&rsquo;s commitment to <strong>aviation modernization, transparency, and efficiency</strong> across the sector.</p>',0,'2025-11-15 13:16:54','2025-12-01 09:32:22'),
(68,'UAE Passport Rules 2025 – Damaged Passports May Lead to Denied Boarding at Dubai, Abu Dhabi & Sharjah Airports','travel news',NULL,'2025-11-15',0,NULL,'<p><strong>Lebanese travelers heading to the UAE</strong> are urged to check their passports carefully after new <strong>UAE immigration regulations</strong> introduced stricter rules on document conditions. Travelers departing from <strong>Dubai International Airport</strong>, <strong>Abu Dhabi Airport</strong>, and <strong>Sharjah Airport</strong> may be <strong>denied boarding</strong> if their passport shows even <strong>minor damage</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This update is part of a global increase in passport security standards affecting passengers from <strong>Lebanon, GCC countries, Europe, and Asia</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>⚠️ What Counts as a Damaged Passport?</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Under UAE regulations, immigration officers can reject passports with:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Torn or loose pages</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Water stains</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Bent or folded covers</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Frayed edges</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Broken or unreadable biometric chips</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Smudged personal information</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Even <strong>minor wear and tear</strong> can be considered suspicious, resulting in denied entry despite having a valid <strong>UAE visa</strong>, <strong>residency</strong>, or <strong>travel itinerary</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>🌍 Global Trend in Passport Security</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>The UAE aligns with strict passport rules enforced in:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The United States</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Australia</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Thailand</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Indonesia</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>The European Union</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Countries worldwide are tightening inspection standards to prevent fraud and ensure secure international travel.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>🧾 Partial vs. Severe Passport Damage</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Immigration authorities typically classify damage as:</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>1. Partial Damage (May Still Cause Delays)</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Examples include:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Slight bends</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Minor stains</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Small tears</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Faded cover</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>These may still cause delays as officers question the document&rsquo;s authenticity.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3><strong>2. Severe Damage (Not Accepted)</strong></h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Cases where the passport is immediately rejected include:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Torn pages</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Water-destroyed pages</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Missing personal data</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Broken electronic chip</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Detached cover</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>In such cases, passengers are <strong>not allowed to board</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>✔️ How Lebanese Travelers Can Protect Their Passports</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>To avoid expensive last-minute issues, travelers should:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Keep passports in protective covers</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Avoid placing them in back pockets or mixed with liquids</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Store them away from heat or moisture</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Never fold or bend them</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Avoid exposing them to perfume, alcohol, or sanitizer (causes discoloration)</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>🔄 When You Should Renew Your Passport</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Authorities recommend renewing in cases of:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Torn pages</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Water damage</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Loose cover</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Chip malfunction</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Fraying edges</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Visible stains or burns</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Lebanese travelers should also ensure <strong>six months validity</strong> before the travel date.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>✈️ Travel Advice for Passengers Flying from Dubai, Abu Dhabi &amp; Sharjah</h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Maintaining a clean and undamaged passport helps avoid:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Denied boarding</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Trip cancellations</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Extra fees</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Visa rejections</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>Immigration delays</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>By taking preventive steps early, travelers can enjoy a <strong>smooth, stress-free travel experience</strong> to the UAE and beyond.</p>',1,'2025-11-15 13:21:16','2025-11-15 13:21:16'),
(69,'Free Starlink Wi-Fi on Emirates: What It Means for Flights from Beirut Meta',NULL,NULL,'2025-12-18',0,NULL,'<h4><strong>The News: High-Speed Internet is Coming to the Skies</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>Emirates has announced a massive upgrade that will change how we fly. Starting <strong>November 2025</strong>, the airline will begin equipping its entire fleet with ultra-fast <strong>Starlink Wi-Fi</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For Lebanese travelers who rely on the Beirut-Dubai route for business or transit, this is a game-changer. The rollout starts with the <strong>Boeing 777</strong> aircraft and will cover the entire fleet by mid-2027.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>Why This Matters for Travelers from Lebanon</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>It&rsquo;s Completely Free:</strong> Unlike previous packages where you had to pay or be a Skywards member, this service is <strong>complimentary for all passengers</strong> in every class.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Stay Connected:</strong> Whether you are scrolling Instagram, finishing a presentation for a meeting in Dubai, or video-calling family back in Beirut, the connection will support streaming and gaming.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Live TV Upgrade:</strong> By late December 2025, Live TV will also be powered by Starlink, ensuring you don&#39;t miss breaking news or live sports while cruising at 35,000 feet.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>Rollout Schedule: When Will You See It?</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>November 2025:</strong> Rollout begins on Boeing 777 aircraft (commonly used on Beirut routes).</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>February 2026:</strong> Installation starts on the A380 superjumbos.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Mid-2027:</strong> Fleet-wide completion expected.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>Emirates President Sir Tim Clark emphasized that this partnership with SpaceX is about delivering a seamless experience, matching the connectivity you enjoy on the ground.</p>',1,'2025-12-18 15:42:31','2025-12-18 15:42:31'),
(70,'Thai Airways Product Launch',NULL,NULL,'2025-12-18',0,NULL,'<h1><strong>Premium Economy Plus&quot;: Lie-Flat Beds for Less on Asia Routes</strong></h1>\r\n\r\n<h2><strong>Affordable Luxury for Your Asian Holiday</strong></h2>\r\n\r\n<p>Thailand is one of the top holiday destinations for Lebanese travelers. If you are planning a multi-stop tour around Asia, <strong>Thai Airways</strong> has just launched a new &quot;sweet spot&quot; for comfort: <strong>Premium Economy Plus</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This new cabin class offers fully <strong>lie-flat beds</strong>&mdash;previously sold as Business Class&mdash;at a Premium Economy price point.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>Where Can You Fly This?</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>While Thai Airways doesn&#39;t fly direct to Beirut, many Lebanese travelers connect through Bangkok (BKK) to reach other parts of Asia. This new product is currently available on regional routes from Bangkok to:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Chennai, Hyderabad, Dhaka, Kathmandu, and Jakarta</strong>.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>If you are booking a side trip from Bangkok to Indonesia (Jakarta) or India, look for this option to get Business Class comfort for a fraction of the price.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>What to Expect Onboard</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>The seats are repurposed from <strong>Virgin Atlantic&rsquo;s &quot;Upper Class&quot;</strong>, featuring a 1-1-1 herringbone layout.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>The Pros:</strong> 20-inch wide seat, fully flat bed, 11.1-inch HD screen, and power outlets.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>The Cons:</strong> It is a &quot;Business Lite&quot; service. You get the seat, but maybe not the full meal service or lounge access (depending on the route).</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p>This move allows Thai Airways to offer &quot;unbundled&quot; luxury, perfect for travelers who want to sleep comfortably without paying for full business class perks.</p>',1,'2025-12-18 15:49:39','2025-12-18 15:49:39'),
(71,'Gen Z Travelers in Lebanon: How to Travel Smart, Cheap & Authentic in 2026',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-17',0,NULL,'<p>Did you know that Gen Z (born 1997&ndash;2012) now makes up nearly <strong>40% of global travelers</strong>? But in Lebanon, the story is different. It&rsquo;s not just about &quot;wanderlust&quot;&mdash;it&rsquo;s about escaping the daily grind, spending &quot;Fresh Dollars&quot; wisely, and finding spots that look amazing on TikTok without breaking the bank.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>This generation is tech-savvy, eco-conscious, and experience-driven. They don&rsquo;t want a generic bus tour; they want <em>freedom</em>.</p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>What Lebanese Gen Z Travelers Actually Value</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>💸 Smart Budgeting (The &quot;Fresh&quot; Factor):</strong> Forget $500/night luxury hotels. Lebanese Gen Z prefers <strong>hostels, eco-lodges, and Airbnb rentals</strong>. They save on sleep to spend on <em>experiences</em>&mdash;like paragliding in Jounieh or street food tours in Istanbul.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>🌍 Sustainable &amp; Local:</strong> More than half of Gen Z prioritizes eco-friendly travel. They&rsquo;d rather support a local family guesthouse in Batroun or Dahab than a massive international chain.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>📱 The &quot;Instagrammable&quot; Moment:</strong> 84% of Gen Z travelers decide where to go based on influencers. If it&rsquo;s not on your story, did it even happen? (Think: The swings in Bali or the balloons in Cappadocia).</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>🎒 Adventure Over Comfort:</strong> From hiking the Lebanon Mountain Trail (LMT) to free-diving in Tyro, this generation wants <strong>active travel</strong>.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>Shifting Trends in 2026</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>&quot;Bleisure&quot; is King:</strong> With remote work becoming normal for Lebanese freelancers, many are combining &quot;Business + Leisure&quot;&mdash;working from a caf&eacute; in Cyprus for a week, then exploring on the weekend.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Visa-Free is a Priority:</strong> Due to embassy delays, Lebanese Gen Z strongly favors destinations like <strong>Turkey, Georgia, and Sharm El Sheikh</strong>.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>Top Destinations for Lebanese Gen Z Right Now</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<ol start=\"1\">\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Bali (Indonesia):</strong> The ultimate digital nomad hub (Visa on Arrival).</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Turkey (Istanbul/Fethiye):</strong> Close, cheap, and no visa required.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Tulum (Mexico):</strong> For those willing to make the long haul for the ultimate vibe.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>How Worldwide Travel (WWTT) Serves Gen Z:</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Customizable &quot;Fresh Fund&quot; Packages:</strong> flexible payment options.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Visa Assistance:</strong> We handle the paperwork so you don&#39;t have to.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>WhatsApp Booking:</strong> No need to call; just text us your dates.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>',1,'2026-01-17 22:43:42','2026-01-17 22:43:42'),
(72,'Jamaica is Back: Why Your Next Corporate Retreat Should Be in the Caribbean',NULL,NULL,'2026-01-18',0,NULL,'<p>Jamaica has made a remarkable return to the <strong>MICE (Meetings, Incentives, Conferences, and Exhibitions)</strong> scene, fully reopening for business travel following the impact of Hurricane Melissa late last year.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>For Lebanese companies looking for an <strong>exclusive incentive destination</strong> that goes beyond the usual spots (like Dubai or Antalya), Jamaica offers a level of prestige that says: <em>&quot;We value our team.&quot;</em></p>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>Resilience Meets Luxury</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>The Jamaica Tourist Board has done an incredible job restoring infrastructure. The island is once again welcoming international meetings and corporate retreats.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Venues are Open:</strong> From world-class convention centers in Montego Bay to boutique resorts in Negril, facilities are ready for events of all sizes.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Connectivity:</strong> International airports are fully operational, ensuring seamless travel for your executives.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>Why Choose Jamaica for Your Lebanese Team?</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>It&rsquo;s not just a meeting; it&rsquo;s an <strong>experience</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Unforgettable Incentives:</strong> After the conference, your team can enjoy catamaran cruises, ziplining through the jungle, or exclusive reggae nights.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>The &quot;Wow&quot; Factor:</strong> Flying your top performers to the Caribbean is the ultimate morale booster in 2026.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h4><strong>The Visa Question: We Handle It.</strong></h4>\r\n\r\n<p>We know what you are thinking: <em>&quot;Do Lebanese need a visa?&quot;</em> <strong>Yes, they do.</strong> But this is where <strong>Worldwide Travel (WWTT)</strong> steps in.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>We manage the entire visa application process for your delegation.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>We ensure all files are compliant with the Jamaican Embassy requirements.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>We handle flight connections (usually via London or Frankfurt) to ensure a smooth journey.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Verdict:</strong> Jamaica&rsquo;s rapid recovery makes it the ideal &quot;Comeback Destination&quot; for 2026. Combine professional facilities with the warmth of the Caribbean for a retreat your team will never forget.</p>',1,'2026-01-17 23:14:38','2026-01-17 23:14:38'),
(73,'Visa-Free Countries for Lebanese Passport Holders in 2026 (The Complete List)','Travel Guides','visa-free-countries-lebanese-passport-2026','2026-01-18',0,NULL,'<p>Let&rsquo;s be honest: Traveling with a Lebanese passport can sometimes feel like an obstacle course. Between embassy appointments, fresh dollar payments, and waiting times, you just want to book a ticket and <strong>go</strong>.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>But here is the good news: <strong>You have more options than you think.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>At <strong>Worldwide Travel (WWTT)</strong>, we have helped thousands of Lebanese travelers explore the world since 2002. We&rsquo;ve compiled the ultimate guide for 2026 on where you can fly directly from Beirut&ndash;Rafic Hariri International Airport without the headache of a rejected visa application.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Whether you are looking for a quick weekend escape or a luxury honeymoon, pack your bags. Here is where you can go.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3><strong>1. The &quot;Just Book &amp; Go&quot; List (Visa-Free)</strong> 🇹🇷 🇯🇴</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><em>No paperwork. No embassy. Just your valid passport and a ticket.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Turkey (T&uuml;rkiye)</strong> The #1 destination for Lebanese. Whether it&rsquo;s shopping in Istanbul, beaches in Antalya, or business in Ankara, you can enter for up to 90 days completely visa-free.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Why go?</strong> Close to Beirut, great food, and amazing value for money.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Flight Time:</strong> ~1 hour 45 mins.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Georgia</strong> Nature, mountains, and incredible food. While rules can change, Lebanese citizens generally enjoy visa-free entry for up to one year.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Why go?</strong> Affordable skiing in winter and stunning greenery in summer.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Jordan</strong> Our neighbor next door. Visit Petra, Wadi Rum, or the Dead Sea.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Note:</strong> Usually visa-free, but always good to check border regulations if crossing by land vs. air.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Ecuador &amp; Dominica</strong> Looking to go further? These countries offer visa-free access, though the flight path will require transit visas (Schengen/USA/UK), so plan carefully!</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3><strong>2. Visa on Arrival (The &quot;Low Stress&quot; List)</strong> 🇲🇻 🇸🇨</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><em>You get the stamp when you land. Usually requires a hotel booking, return ticket, and some cash (USD).</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>The Maldives</strong> The dream honeymoon destination. Lebanese citizens get a visa on arrival for up to 30 days.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Requirement:</strong> Confirmed hotel booking + Return ticket.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Seychelles</strong> Another paradise island. Visitor&rsquo;s permit issued on arrival.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Requirement:</strong> Proof of accommodation + Sufficient funds.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Nepal</strong> For the adventurers. You can get a visa on arrival at Kathmandu airport.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3><strong>3. Easy E-Visas (Apply Online from Home)</strong> 🇦🇪 🇶🇦</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><em>No embassy visits. We can handle this for you in minutes.</em></p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>UAE (Dubai / Abu Dhabi)</strong> While not visa-free, the process is fast.</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>How we help:</strong> Send us your passport copy via WhatsApp, and we handle the application for your 30 or 60-day visa.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Qatar &amp; Oman</strong> Simple online procedures that are usually approved quickly for Lebanese residents.</p>\r\n\r\n<hr />\r\n<h3><strong>4. What About Europe? (Schengen Visa Help)</strong> 🇪🇺</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Do you have your heart set on Paris, Rome, or Athens? While Europe is not visa-free, <strong>it is not impossible.</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<p>The mistake most people make is <strong>incomplete files</strong>. A missing hotel confirmation or unclear bank statement leads to rejection.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>How Worldwide Travel Helps You:</strong></p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>We review your file to ensure it meets Embassy standards.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>We assist with appointment scheduling.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>We handle your flight and hotel reservations for the visa application.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p>We provide <strong>Travel Insurance</strong> (mandatory for Schengen).</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Don&#39;t Let Your Passport Stop You.</strong> Whether you want a visa-free trip to Turkey or need help securing a Schengen Visa for France, <strong>Worldwide Travel</strong> is your partner in Ain El Mreisseh.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>We accept <strong>Fresh USD</strong> and offer the most competitive ticketing rates in Lebanon.</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Ready to fly?</strong> 👉 <a href=\"https://api.whatsapp.com/send/?phone=96179119311&amp;text&amp;type=phone_number&amp;app_absent=0\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Click Here to WhatsApp Us</strong>&nbsp;</a>for a quote on your next trip! 📞 <strong>Call us:</strong> +961 1 365931 📍 <strong>Visit us:</strong> Ibn Sina Str., Ain El Mreisseh, Beirut</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>&nbsp;</h3>',0,'2026-01-18 21:12:47','2026-01-18 21:14:26'),
(76,'Register for EuroPCR 2026 Paris | Stress-Free Travel from Lebanon','explore',NULL,'2026-02-10',0,NULL,'<h3>Join the World&rsquo;s Leading Interventional Cardiovascular Congress this May.</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Planning your trip from Beirut to Paris for <strong>EuroPCR 2026</strong>? Don&#39;t let logistics slow you down. <strong>Worldwide Travel &amp; Tourism</strong> specializes in comprehensive travel management for medical professionals in Lebanon. We ensure you stay focused on the latest cardiovascular innovations while we handle the details.</p>\r\n\r\n<p>Our <strong>EuroPCR 2026 Travel Package</strong> includes:</p>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Schengen Visa Assistance:</strong> Expert guidance for Lebanese applicants to ensure timely processing.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Flight &amp; Hotel Booking:</strong> Strategic stays near the Palais des Congr&egrave;s de Paris.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Congress Registration:</strong> Direct handling of your EuroPCR passes.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n	<li>\r\n	<p><strong>Seamless Transfers:</strong> Coordination of all ground transportation and local arrangements.</p>\r\n	</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Call to Action:</strong> Ready to secure your spot in Paris? Contact our dedicated corporate team at <strong>tours@worldwidetravel-lb.com</strong> and we&rsquo;ll take care of the rest!</p>',1,'2026-02-10 12:15:15','2026-02-10 12:15:15');
