(48,'Albania Tour from Lebanon','Albania','1315 USD','8 Days / 7 Nights',0,NULL,'Albania-Tour-from-Lebanon-|-8D/7N,-5-Star,-Private-Driver-878250H02030198','<h1>Albania Heritage &amp; Adriatic Wonders &ndash; 8 Days / 7 Nights (From Lebanon)</h1>\r\n\r\n<p>Discover the best of Albania on an <strong>Albania tour package from Lebanon</strong> designed for comfort, culture, and coast. This premium <strong>Albania 8 days 7 nights tour</strong> blends UNESCO-listed heritage with Adriatic beach time, staying in curated <strong>5-star hotel Albania</strong> options and traveling with a <strong>private driver</strong> for seamless transfers.</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Why Lebanese Travelers Love This Trip</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>8D/7N depth</strong> &ndash; see more than a short break; balanced pace across city, heritage, and coast.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Private driver tour</strong> &ndash; safe, comfortable point-to-point travel with flexible stops.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>5-star stays</strong> &ndash; handpicked hotels in Tirana, Berat, and Durres for top comfort.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Guided heritage</strong> &ndash; true <strong>Albania heritage tour</strong> covering <strong>Tirana &amp; Berat UNESCO</strong> sights.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Adriatic leisure</strong> &ndash; enjoy a sunny <strong>Durres Adriatic coast holiday</strong> at the end.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Visa &amp; insurance assistance</strong> &ndash; clear guidance for Lebanese passport holders.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Great value</strong> &ndash; limited-time <strong>Albania holiday starting at $1,315</strong> per person (twin share).</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>At a Glance</h2>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Route:</strong> Tirana &rarr; Kruja &amp; <strong>Dajti mountain trip</strong> &rarr; Berat (UNESCO) &rarr; Durres (Adriatic coast)</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Style:</strong> <strong>Albania private driver tour</strong> with licensed local guides in key cities</p>\r\n\r\n<p><strong>Ideal For:</strong> Couples, families, and small groups seeking an <strong>Albania all-inclusive package Lebanon</strong> style trip</p>\r\n\r\n<h2>Trip Highlights</h2>\r\n\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li><strong>Tirana</strong> &ndash; Skanderbeg Square, Bunk&rsquo;Art, New Bazaar, caf&eacute; culture.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Kruja</strong> &ndash; castle &amp; bazaar, Skanderbeg Museum, artisan crafts.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Dajti Mountain</strong> &ndash; scenic cable car and viewpoints above the capital.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Berat (UNESCO)</strong> &ndash; &ldquo;City of a Thousand Windows,&rdquo; castle quarter, Onufri Museum.</li>\r\n	<li><strong>Durres</strong> &ndash; Roman amphitheatre, seaside promenade, Adriatic beach time.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n\r\n<h2>Day-by-Day Itinerary (8D/7N)</h2>\r\n\r\n<h3>Day 1 &ndash; Arrival in Tirana</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Meet &amp; greet at the airport and private transfer to your 5-star hotel. Evening stroll and dinner suggestions.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Day 2 &ndash; Tirana City Highlights</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Guided tour: Bunk&rsquo;Art or House of Leaves, New Bazaar, Pyramid of Tirana, Grand Park. Coffee/photo stops included.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Day 3 &ndash; Kruja &amp; Dajti Mountain Trip</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Morning in Kruja Castle and bazaar; afternoon cable car up Dajti for views and sunset (weather-dependent).</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Day 4 &ndash; Transfer to Berat (UNESCO)</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Drive to Berat; explore the castle quarter, Onufri Icon Museum, and Mangalem/Gorica quarters. Boutique 5-star stay where available.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Day 5 &ndash; Berat Heritage Tour</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Deeper walking tour with a local guide. Optional winery visit or cooking class featuring Albanian cuisine.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Day 6 &ndash; Durres Adriatic Coast Holiday</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Private transfer to Durres. Visit the Roman amphitheatre and enjoy beach time on the Adriatic.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Day 7 &ndash; Durres at Leisure</h3>\r\n\r\n<p>Free day for the beach, spa, or a short coastal excursion. Final seaside dinner.</p>\r\n\r\n<h3>Day 8 &ndash; Departure</h